					  Home » Products » New Firearms » Handguns » Semi Automatic » Desert Eagle 1911G #436
                        Desert Eagle 1911G #436
                        $659.00
            				DESCRIPTION:	 
	Featuring all the timeless style of an American original and sharing the proud heritage of the legendary Desert Eagle, the new .45 ACP 1911 from Magnum Research comes fully equipped with top-of-the-line custom features at a basic model price that blows away the competition.
			The Desert Eagle 1911 single action models are shipped with two 8 round magazines with extended base pads for positive magazine insertion. The frame is precision cast and machined from high quality carbon steel and the slide is machined from solid billets of steel than finished in a matte black. The Desert Eagle 1911 comes loaded with outstanding features that would cost extra from a custom gunsmith. Some of these features include a high-ride beavertail grip safety, extended magazine release, aluminum trigger with an overtravel stop, stainless steel full-length guide rod, extended thumb safety, enlarged ejection port, beveled magazine well and double-diamond checkered wood grips held in place by stainless steel hex screws.
	DETAILS:	 
	Model:	DE1911G
	Caliber:	.45 ACP
	Action:	Single-Action
	Capacity:	8+1
	Unloaded Weight:	36.2 oz
	Overall Length:	8.625"
	Barrel Length:	5.055"
	Frame Material:	Steel
	Sights:	High profile sculptured sights w/ horizontal serrations
	Grips:	Wood, double-diamond checkered
	Finish:	Blued Steel
	Includes:	(2) 8-round magazines, lock, manual, hard case
							TEMPORARILY OUT OF STOCK

    60 DAY LAY-AWAY PLAN:
Velocity Works, LLC offers a very convenient Lay-away Plan for our customers. The policies and procedures for our “Lay-away Plan” are as follows:
	Only firearms are eligible for this program.
	Lay-away Agreement(s) require a minimum initial non-refundable deposit of (20%) twenty percent.
	$200 minimum purchase is required.
	During the 60-day period, you may make several smaller payments or one final payment at the end of the 60 days.
	Custom Order(s) or orders for merchandise not in current stock may NOT (at Velocity Works, LLC discretion) be ordered until Eighty percent (80%) of the TOTAL amount of the Velocity Works, LLC Lay-away Agreement(s) is paid.
	Velocity Works, LLC will give store credit for any Lay-away deposit and subsequent payments, if any, when, before the end of the Lay-away period the Buyer wishes to apply their layaway to a different product. This is only applicable if the original Lay-away Agreement(s) was NOT for a USED product or if it is a Custom Order, and the order for the product has not yet been placed with the distributor by Velocity Works, LLC.
	Velocity Works, LLC will refund any payments, NOT including non-refundable deposit and or service fee(s) (if any), provided the Lay-away Agreement(s) was for product not normally stocked in store (ie. custom ordered product) and has NOT yet been ordered.
	Should Buyer be unable to successfully complete a NICS Background Check, Velocity Works, LLC will refund any payments, NOT including non-refundable deposit, or service fee(s), if any.
	Lay-away Agreement(s) will terminate, and BUYER’s deposit and other payments under Lay-away Agreement(s) will become NON-REFUNDABLE and be FORFEITED to Velocity Works, LLC if payment is not received on or before the sixtieth (60th) day of the date of signed Lay-away Agreement(s). There will be no exceptions.
	There are NO REFUNDS of any Lay-away Agreement(s) payments beyond what is stated in this agreement.
	All Lay-away Agreement(s) require that the Lay-away Agreement(s) document be signed and dated.
CONSIGNMENT :
Consignor agrees to place the items listed below on consignment with Velocity Works, LLC to try to sell them under the terms of this agreement. Velocity Works, LLC agrees to accept the items listed for consignment sale under the terms of this agreement. Velocity Works, LLC will:
	Inspect all of the items listed in this agreement, and will determine condition and functionality.
	Write up the description and specifications necessary in order to offer the items for sale.
	Will advertise and offer the items for sale as it deems appropriate.
When the items consigned are sold and final payment is made by the buyer, the Consignor will receive their net amount within 30 days. The Consignor represents that they are the rightful owner of the items listed, and that the items are free of any encumbrance. The Consignor agrees that, as Velocity Works, LLC is required to complete all inspections and specifications, prepare the items for sale, and advertise the items, that the items consigned will be left on consignment with Velocity Works, LLC for a minimum of 60 days.
 
After 60 days, if not sold, consignor must pick up firearm or renew agreement in person within 15 days. After 15 days a $5.00 per daystorage fee will be assessed, NO EXCEPTIONS! If firearm is not picked up within 30 days after agreement expires, the firearm becomes property of Velocity Works, LLC.While this agreement is in effect, Consignor agrees to grant the exclusive right to market and sell the items listed below to Velocity Works, LLC.
 
ALL ITEMS MUST BE IN GOOD CONDITION AND CLEAN: Consignee reserves the right not to display any consigned item found on close inspection to be defective. Such items not reclaimed by the consignor within five days of notification, the firearm will become property of Velocity Works, LLC.
 
LIABILITY: Consignee shall not be liable to Consignor for any loss or damage suffered to Consignor's merchandise, including, but limited to, loss or damage to such merchandise from fire, theft, or other casualty. Consignor hereby releases Consignee to the fullest extent possible from any and all claims or any nature in connection with or arising from the placement of Consignor's merchandise with Consignee. Consignor further covenants that he/she shall make no claim against Consignee or Consignee's insurance carrier for any damage to Consignor's merchandise.
 
If the Consignor decides to have consigned items returned, Federal Law requires that the Consignor complete all appropriate forms as if they were purchasing the firearms and pass the NICS background check and consignor agrees to pay Velocity Works, LLC $25.00 for transfer fees. If consignor fails either the documentation or NICS check the firearm becomes the permanent property of Velocity Works, LLC.
 
Store only consignment fee shall be 15% of the selling price of the item. Fees for other services provided by Velocity Works, LLC (e.g.cleaning or repair) or for services provided by third-party vendors are additional and are not included in the consignment fee.
Online Sales only are available for 20% commission, plus auction fees. A $10.00 upfront charge for online auction is non-refundable for firearm storage, unless firearm sells. All firearms will be listed with the reserve at the consignor’s minimum acceptable price, plus 20%. Auction must be finalized for payment to be released.
 
Store with Online Sale is available for 25% of the selling price, plus auction fees. All firearms will be listed with the reserve at the consignor’s minimum acceptable price, plus 30%. Auction must be finalized for payment to be released.
 
After 15% in-store, 20% online or 30% in store with internet, plus auction fees is deducted from selling price, a check will be issued for the remaining balance to consignor. If consignor does not pick up check within 14 days, check will be mailed to their address of record on file via U.S.P.S. for an additional fee of $5.00.

					  Home » Products » New Firearms » Rifles » Semi Automatic Rifles » HENRY US SURVIVAL TAKEDOWN .22LR   #264
                        HENRY US SURVIVAL TAKEDOWN .22LR   #264
                        $299.00
            				DESCRIPTION:	 
	Since 1959, the venerable AR-7 has been the choice of U.S. Air Force pilots who need a small-caliber rifle they can count on for survival should they have to punch out over a remote area.  Over the years, the AR-7's reputation for portability, ease of operation and reliability has carried over to the civilian world as well.
			 
			Like the original Henry US Survival Rifle, our latest take on this innovative, semi-automatic rifle is lightweight (just 3.5 lbs) and highly portable.  At just 16.5" long (when all the components are stowed) it fits easily into the cargo area of a plane or boat or in a backpack.  And because it's chambered in .22LR you can carry a large quantity of ammunition, without adding much weight to your gear.
			 
			When disassembled, the pieces fit inside the impact-resistant, water-resistant stock.  Assembly is as easy as attaching the receiver to the stock, inserting the barrel and screwing on the barrel nut.  In just a few seconds, without the need for any tools, the Henry U.S. Survival AR-7 is ready for action.
			 
	DETAILS:	 
	Model:	U.S. Survival AR-7 Camo
	Caliber:	.22 LR
	Action:	Semi-automatic
	Capacity:	8-round magazine
	Weight:	3.5 lbs
	Overall Length:	35 in assembled, 16.5 in when stowed
	Barrel Length:	15.5"
	Sights:	Adjustable rear, blade front
	Safety Selector:	Rear of action, right side
	Stock:	Synthetic, camo
	Includes:	(2) 8-round magazines

					  Home » Products » Gun Cleaning
			Complete gun cleaning and inspecting isn't just for an old gun found hidden in the attic. It is part of regular maintenance and seasonal activity.
			Complete gun cleaning and inspecting includes:
				Disassembly of the entire gun.
	Removing old lubricante
	Cleaning out dirt and powder residue from the working parts and the barrel
	Inspection of all working parts for excessive wear, metal fatigue, bends, cracks, or breakage.
	We will contact you if there are any problems with the inspection and explain what can or should be done before re-assembling the firearm.
				Reassemble, lubricate, and apply protective oils to all working parts
	Apply protective oils to all exterior metal parts
	Clean and inspect stocks and grips for ware, cracks or other issues
	We will contact you if there are any problems with the inspection and explain what can or should be done
	Apply appropriate wax, oils, or protectant to the stock or grips
			Cleaning does not include removal of rust and refinishing. I am happy to discuss and refinish your firearm also.
			Pricing varies depending on the gun so please contact us for an estimate.

					  Home » Products » Buying A Firearm Online
    When a customer purchases a firearm online, we cannot ship the firearm directly to the customer under federal law.  The customer must make arrangements with a FFL in their area to accept the shipment and transfer the firearm.  FFLs usually charge a fee for this service, which varies from dealer to dealer
 
We can not ship out a firearm until we receive a copy of the FFL license from the customer's selected FFL.  It is the customer's responsibility to arrange the transfer with their selected FFL.
 
Below is Velocity Works' contact information, which the customer must provide to their selected FFL to ensure we get a copy of their license.  Make sure to have the FFL reference the order # and customer name.  In the comments section of the order, please indicate where you would like the firearm sent so we can cross reference the information.  Once payment is processed and we have a copy of the FFL license in hand, we will ship out the order.
 
FFL licenses may be emailed to firearms@velocityworks.net or faxed to 1-877-287-0089.
 
For any questions/concerns, please call us at (614)-891-4545 or email us at firearms@velocityworks.net , we are happy to assist you!

					  Home » Products » Pre-owned Firearms » Handguns » Semi Automatic » CZ MODEL 83 .380   #269
                        CZ MODEL 83 .380   #269
                        $379.00
            				DESCRIPTION:	 
	The micro-sized .380s that have arrived on the scene in recent years have reduced dimensions to the point that they are difficult to control even for the most accomplished shooters. The CZ 83's combination of small size and moderate weight easily handles the new generation of high-performance defensive ammo that has become available for 'pocket' pistol calibers from leading ammo manufacturers. The DA/SA trigger mechanism operates in the same manner as the CZ 75. The 83 can be carried 'cocked and locked' with the hammer back and the safety on for single action operation, or it may be manually decocked for hammer-down carry. When carried in the decocked position, the safety lever does not need to be de-activated, but instead the first shot is double action and subsequent shots are single action. The CZ 83 features an ambidextrous manual safety and magazine catch.
			 
			Along with its superior shootability, the 83 boasts twice the magazine capacity (12+1 in .380) of its tiny competitors.
	DETAILS:	 
	Model:	CZ 83
	Caliber:	.380 Auto
	Action:	Single/Double-action
	Capacity:	12+1
	Unloaded Weight:	1.76 lbs
	Overall Length:	6.77 in
	Barrel Length:	3.82 in
	Frame Material:	Steel
	Sights:	Fixed
	Grips:	Black molded plastic
	Finish:	Blued
	Includes:	(1) 12-round magazine

					  Home » Products » New Firearms » Rifles » Semi Automatic Rifles » HENRY US SURVIVAL TAKEDOWN .22LR   #264
                        HENRY US SURVIVAL TAKEDOWN .22LR   #264
                        $299.00
            				DESCRIPTION:	 
	Since 1959, the venerable AR-7 has been the choice of U.S. Air Force pilots who need a small-caliber rifle they can count on for survival should they have to punch out over a remote area.  Over the years, the AR-7's reputation for portability, ease of operation and reliability has carried over to the civilian world as well.
			 
			Like the original Henry US Survival Rifle, our latest take on this innovative, semi-automatic rifle is lightweight (just 3.5 lbs) and highly portable.  At just 16.5" long (when all the components are stowed) it fits easily into the cargo area of a plane or boat or in a backpack.  And because it's chambered in .22LR you can carry a large quantity of ammunition, without adding much weight to your gear.
			 
			When disassembled, the pieces fit inside the impact-resistant, water-resistant stock.  Assembly is as easy as attaching the receiver to the stock, inserting the barrel and screwing on the barrel nut.  In just a few seconds, without the need for any tools, the Henry U.S. Survival AR-7 is ready for action.
			 
	DETAILS:	 
	Model:	U.S. Survival AR-7 Camo
	Caliber:	.22 LR
	Action:	Semi-automatic
	Capacity:	8-round magazine
	Weight:	3.5 lbs
	Overall Length:	35 in assembled, 16.5 in when stowed
	Barrel Length:	15.5"
	Sights:	Adjustable rear, blade front
	Safety Selector:	Rear of action, right side
	Stock:	Synthetic, camo
	Includes:	(2) 8-round magazines

					  Home » Products » Transfers
    Velocity Works is happy to provide FFL transfer services for its customers.  We will need to send your seller a copy of our FFL before they can ship out your item.  When it arrives, we’ll contact you and run a background check in our shop when you come to pick up the item.  When the background check clears, we collect the transfer fee, and the firearm is yours.  The time from when you walk in to when you walk out with your firearm is usually less than 30 minutes.  We will need a few pieces of information to get the process started.  It is easiest if you send us an email to Firearms@VelocityWorks.net with the information. 
What we need from you:
	Your name
	Your phone number
	Your email address
	The seller’s name or business name
	The seller’s phone # and/or email address
	What you are buying (we don’t need much here, make and model will usually suffice)
Transfer Fees
The fee for our FFL transfer service (long gun, hand gun, or receiver) is $20.00.  If you have more than one firearm you would like to have transferred, the fee is $20.00 for the 1st firearm plus $10.00 per each additional firearm transferred in the same transaction. We must collect sales tax on all transfer fees.
If you have any questions, please don’t hesitate to inquire at Firearms@VelocityWorks.net or 614-891-4545

                        Glock 42 380ACP NEW #412
                        $429.00
            				DESCRIPTION:	 
	The new Glock 42, in .380 Auto, is a slimline subcompact pistol engineered with the Glock Perfection promise and able to withstand the rigors of routine training.  Made in the USA, the G42 is the smallest pistol Glock has ever introduced, making it ideal for pocket carry and shooters with smaller hands.  Years of requests across market groups for a super-concealable, reliable single-stack .380 Glock pistol prompted extensive research and development to bring the Glock customer the G42.
	DETAILS:	 
	Model:	G42
	Caliber:	.380 Auto
	Action:	Striker-fire
	Capacity:	6+1
	Unloaded Weight:	13.76 oz
	Overall Length:	5.94"
	Barrel Length:	3.25"
	Frame Material:	Polymer
	Sights:	Rear notch, front dot
	Grips:	Gen4 Stippling
	Finish:	Black
	Includes:	(2) 6-round magazines, plastic case, papers, lock, brush

    60 DAY LAY-AWAY PLAN:
Velocity Works, LLC offers a very convenient Lay-away Plan for our customers. The policies and procedures for our “Lay-away Plan” are as follows:
	Only firearms are eligible for this program.
	Lay-away Agreement(s) require a minimum initial non-refundable deposit of (20%) twenty percent.
	$200 minimum purchase is required.
	During the 60-day period, you may make several smaller payments or one final payment at the end of the 60 days.
	Custom Order(s) or orders for merchandise not in current stock may NOT (at Velocity Works, LLC discretion) be ordered until Eighty percent (80%) of the TOTAL amount of the Velocity Works, LLC Lay-away Agreement(s) is paid.
	Velocity Works, LLC will give store credit for any Lay-away deposit and subsequent payments, if any, when, before the end of the Lay-away period the Buyer wishes to apply their layaway to a different product. This is only applicable if the original Lay-away Agreement(s) was NOT for a USED product or if it is a Custom Order, and the order for the product has not yet been placed with the distributor by Velocity Works, LLC.
	Velocity Works, LLC will refund any payments, NOT including non-refundable deposit and or service fee(s) (if any), provided the Lay-away Agreement(s) was for product not normally stocked in store (ie. custom ordered product) and has NOT yet been ordered.
	Should Buyer be unable to successfully complete a NICS Background Check, Velocity Works, LLC will refund any payments, NOT including non-refundable deposit, or service fee(s), if any.
	Lay-away Agreement(s) will terminate, and BUYER’s deposit and other payments under Lay-away Agreement(s) will become NON-REFUNDABLE and be FORFEITED to Velocity Works, LLC if payment is not received on or before the sixtieth (60th) day of the date of signed Lay-away Agreement(s). There will be no exceptions.
	There are NO REFUNDS of any Lay-away Agreement(s) payments beyond what is stated in this agreement.
	All Lay-away Agreement(s) require that the Lay-away Agreement(s) document be signed and dated.
CONSIGNMENT :
Consignor agrees to place the items listed below on consignment with Velocity Works, LLC to try to sell them under the terms of this agreement. Velocity Works, LLC agrees to accept the items listed for consignment sale under the terms of this agreement. Velocity Works, LLC will:
	Inspect all of the items listed in this agreement, and will determine condition and functionality.
	Write up the description and specifications necessary in order to offer the items for sale.
	Will advertise and offer the items for sale as it deems appropriate.
When the items consigned are sold and final payment is made by the buyer, the Consignor will receive their net amount within 30 days. The Consignor represents that they are the rightful owner of the items listed, and that the items are free of any encumbrance. The Consignor agrees that, as Velocity Works, LLC is required to complete all inspections and specifications, prepare the items for sale, and advertise the items, that the items consigned will be left on consignment with Velocity Works, LLC for a minimum of 60 days.
 
After 60 days, if not sold, consignor must pick up firearm or renew agreement in person within 15 days. After 15 days a $5.00 per daystorage fee will be assessed, NO EXCEPTIONS! If firearm is not picked up within 30 days after agreement expires, the firearm becomes property of Velocity Works, LLC.While this agreement is in effect, Consignor agrees to grant the exclusive right to market and sell the items listed below to Velocity Works, LLC.
 
ALL ITEMS MUST BE IN GOOD CONDITION AND CLEAN: Consignee reserves the right not to display any consigned item found on close inspection to be defective. Such items not reclaimed by the consignor within five days of notification, the firearm will become property of Velocity Works, LLC.
 
LIABILITY: Consignee shall not be liable to Consignor for any loss or damage suffered to Consignor's merchandise, including, but limited to, loss or damage to such merchandise from fire, theft, or other casualty. Consignor hereby releases Consignee to the fullest extent possible from any and all claims or any nature in connection with or arising from the placement of Consignor's merchandise with Consignee. Consignor further covenants that he/she shall make no claim against Consignee or Consignee's insurance carrier for any damage to Consignor's merchandise.
 
If the Consignor decides to have consigned items returned, Federal Law requires that the Consignor complete all appropriate forms as if they were purchasing the firearms and pass the NICS background check and consignor agrees to pay Velocity Works, LLC $25.00 for transfer fees. If consignor fails either the documentation or NICS check the firearm becomes the permanent property of Velocity Works, LLC.
 
Store only consignment fee shall be 15% of the selling price of the item. Fees for other services provided by Velocity Works, LLC (e.g.cleaning or repair) or for services provided by third-party vendors are additional and are not included in the consignment fee.
Online Sales only are available for 20% commission, plus auction fees. A $10.00 upfront charge for online auction is non-refundable for firearm storage, unless firearm sells. All firearms will be listed with the reserve at the consignor’s minimum acceptable price, plus 20%. Auction must be finalized for payment to be released.
 
Store with Online Sale is available for 25% of the selling price, plus auction fees. All firearms will be listed with the reserve at the consignor’s minimum acceptable price, plus 30%. Auction must be finalized for payment to be released.
 
After 15% in-store, 20% online or 30% in store with internet, plus auction fees is deducted from selling price, a check will be issued for the remaining balance to consignor. If consignor does not pick up check within 14 days, check will be mailed to their address of record on file via U.S.P.S. for an additional fee of $5.00.

Rest assured that we will not share any personal information with any outside companies. Your information is safe with us.

					  Home » Products » Buying A Firearm Online
    When a customer purchases a firearm online, we cannot ship the firearm directly to the customer under federal law.  The customer must make arrangements with a FFL in their area to accept the shipment and transfer the firearm.  FFLs usually charge a fee for this service, which varies from dealer to dealer
 
We can not ship out a firearm until we receive a copy of the FFL license from the customer's selected FFL.  It is the customer's responsibility to arrange the transfer with their selected FFL.
 
Below is Velocity Works' contact information, which the customer must provide to their selected FFL to ensure we get a copy of their license.  Make sure to have the FFL reference the order # and customer name.  In the comments section of the order, please indicate where you would like the firearm sent so we can cross reference the information.  Once payment is processed and we have a copy of the FFL license in hand, we will ship out the order.
 
FFL licenses may be emailed to firearms@velocityworks.net or faxed to 1-877-287-0089.
 
For any questions/concerns, please call us at (614)-891-4545 or email us at firearms@velocityworks.net , we are happy to assist you!

					  Home » Products » New Firearms » Rifles » Semi Automatic Rifles » HENRY US SURVIVAL TAKEDOWN .22LR   #264
                        HENRY US SURVIVAL TAKEDOWN .22LR   #264
                        $299.00
            				DESCRIPTION:	 
	Since 1959, the venerable AR-7 has been the choice of U.S. Air Force pilots who need a small-caliber rifle they can count on for survival should they have to punch out over a remote area.  Over the years, the AR-7's reputation for portability, ease of operation and reliability has carried over to the civilian world as well.
			 
			Like the original Henry US Survival Rifle, our latest take on this innovative, semi-automatic rifle is lightweight (just 3.5 lbs) and highly portable.  At just 16.5" long (when all the components are stowed) it fits easily into the cargo area of a plane or boat or in a backpack.  And because it's chambered in .22LR you can carry a large quantity of ammunition, without adding much weight to your gear.
			 
			When disassembled, the pieces fit inside the impact-resistant, water-resistant stock.  Assembly is as easy as attaching the receiver to the stock, inserting the barrel and screwing on the barrel nut.  In just a few seconds, without the need for any tools, the Henry U.S. Survival AR-7 is ready for action.
			 
	DETAILS:	 
	Model:	U.S. Survival AR-7 Camo
	Caliber:	.22 LR
	Action:	Semi-automatic
	Capacity:	8-round magazine

description: Since 1959, the venerable AR-7 has been the choice of U.S. Air Force pilots who need a small-caliber rifle they can count on for survival should they have to punch out over a remote area. Over the years, the AR-7's reputation for portability, ease of operation and reliability has carried over to the civilian world as well.   Like the original Henry US Survival Rifle, our latest take on this innovative, semi-automatic rifle is lightweight (just 3.5 lbs) and highly portable. At just 16.5" long (when all the components are stowed) it fits easily into the cargo area of a plane or boat or in a backpack. And because it's chambered in .22LR you can carry a large quantity of ammunition, without adding much weight to your gear.   When disassembled, the pieces fit inside the impact-resistant, water-resistant stock. Assembly is as easy as attaching the receiver to the stock, inserting the barrel and screwing on the barrel nut. In just a few seconds, without the need for any tools, the Henry U.S. Survival AR-7 is ready for action.

                        ROSSI R223 .223   #203 -
                        $259.00
            				DESCRIPTION:	 
	Rossi Single Shot Rifles combine simplicity, accuracy and practicality in a rifle built for generations of shooting enjoyment. Each of these rifles is equipped with a scope rail and hammer extension that accommodates all popular optics. The heavy barrel models are button rifled for extreme accuracy. Rossi varmint rifles and their standard profile counterparts all feature a black synthetic stock with removable cheek piece and are equipped with Rossi’s soft recoil pad and distinctive white line spacer, button rifled barrels, adjustable fiber optic sights and sling swivels. Centerfire models have an extra wide positive action extractor to ensure easy removal of the spent case when you open the breech, while the rimfire models carry a powerful ejector that reliably kicks the spent or unfired shell clear. These rifles combine four safety systems to make them as safe and enjoyable as possible. The Rossi single shot rifle incorporates a transfer bar mechanism that stops the hammer from striking the firing pin unless the hammer has been cocked and trigger has been pulled completely rearward. This helps prevent accidental firing from drops or impact. All Rossi rifles incorporate our breech lock system, which prevents the action from being opened or closed when the hammer is cocked, along with our manual hammer block safety and Taurus Security System. Over 100 years of firearms design has taught us that safety comes first and foremost. Every Rossi full-size and youth-size rifle is equipped with fully adjustable fiber optic sights and are drilled and tapped to accommodate the Rossi scope mount base. These single shot rifles are perfect for training first-time shooters, fun and affordable target shooting and all types of hunting.

	Model:	R223
	Caliber:	.223 Rem
	Action:	Break open
	Capacity:	Single shot
	Overall Length:	38.5 in
	Barrel Length:	22 in
	Sights:	Adjustable fiber optic, green rear, red front
	Stock:	Black synthetic with removable cheek rest

			Complete gun cleaning and inspecting isn't just for an old gun found hidden in the attic. It is part of regular maintenance and seasonal activity.
			Complete gun cleaning and inspecting includes:
				Disassembly of the entire gun.
	Removing old lubricante
	Cleaning out dirt and powder residue from the working parts and the barrel
	Inspection of all working parts for excessive wear, metal fatigue, bends, cracks, or breakage.
	We will contact you if there are any problems with the inspection and explain what can or should be done before re-assembling the firearm.
				Reassemble, lubricate, and apply protective oils to all working parts
	Apply protective oils to all exterior metal parts
	Clean and inspect stocks and grips for ware, cracks or other issues
	We will contact you if there are any problems with the inspection and explain what can or should be done
	Apply appropriate wax, oils, or protectant to the stock or grips
			Cleaning does not include removal of rust and refinishing. I am happy to discuss and refinish your firearm also.
			Pricing varies depending on the gun so please contact us for an estimate.

			Gunsmithing
			Find an old gun in the closet that you don't know if it works? Maybe a firearm of yours made an odd noise, and now it doesn't seem to cycle correctly. We can check it out and repair most problems that show up from regular firearm use, or  long periods of inactivity.
			The stock or grips of your gun looking dull, worn, or dirtied? We can clean and refinish the wood on any type of firearm.
			Is your gun's  finish worn, scratched, pitted, or rusted? We can take care of the problem and refinish it in classic bluing and more advanced DuraCoat.
			Gun Cleaning
			Complete gun cleaning and inspecting can be for both regular maintenance for seasonal activity, or for an old gun found hidden in the attic.
				 	
			Stock Refinishing
			Stock cleaning and refinishing for shotguns, rifles, and handguns.
			Gun Repair
			Gun not cycling correctly, locking up randomly, and not ejecting cases easily can all be due to a broken or missing part.
				 	
			Rebluing and Gun Refinishing
			Firearm rebluing and gun refinishing
	Our gunsmith is a  graduate of Pennsylvania Gunsmith School's Master Gunsmithing program.

					  Home » Products » Transfers
    Velocity Works is happy to provide FFL transfer services for its customers.  We will need to send your seller a copy of our FFL before they can ship out your item.  When it arrives, we’ll contact you and run a background check in our shop when you come to pick up the item.  When the background check clears, we collect the transfer fee, and the firearm is yours.  The time from when you walk in to when you walk out with your firearm is usually less than 30 minutes.  We will need a few pieces of information to get the process started.  It is easiest if you send us an email to Firearms@VelocityWorks.net with the information. 
What we need from you:
	Your name
	Your phone number
	Your email address
	The seller’s name or business name
	The seller’s phone # and/or email address
	What you are buying (we don’t need much here, make and model will usually suffice)
Transfer Fees
The fee for our FFL transfer service (long gun, hand gun, or receiver) is $20.00.  If you have more than one firearm you would like to have transferred, the fee is $20.00 for the 1st firearm plus $10.00 per each additional firearm transferred in the same transaction. We must collect sales tax on all transfer fees.
If you have any questions, please don’t hesitate to inquire at Firearms@VelocityWorks.net or 614-891-4545

					  Home » Products » Pre-owned Firearms » Rifles » Bolt Action Rifles » VW Sniper Mosin #381
                        VW Sniper Mosin #381
                        $1,099.00
            				DESCRIPTION:	 
	Velocity Works is proud to offer the custom-built VW Sniper Mosin Nagant.
			 
			The objective of this custom-built rifle was to produce a capable and attractive heavy caliber, long-range precision target rifle that fires inexpensive ammo and can be had for hundreds less than an off-the-shelf item in the same category.
			 
			We started with a conventional 91-30 round-receiver Mosin Nagant.  We then removed the action and barrel from the wood stock, and completely degreased, cleaned, inspected, and function checked the firearm.  All the steel was then polished and professionally hot blued on site to bring out the luster of the steel and protect from corrosion.
			 
			For mounting optics, we went with a top-of-the-line picatinny scope mount.  These heavy duty mounts are precision machined out of 6061 aluminum here in the USA.  The mount utilizes 3 mounting points and has a hard coating to resist chips, scratches and corrosion.  These mounts have been tested up to 800 yards with sub-MOA results, quite impressive considering the kick of a 7.62x54R round.  We had the mount professionally installed by our on-sight gunsmith, who measures, fits the parts, and drills and taps the necessary holes to secure the mount. Included with the mount is a custom down-turned bolt handle which allows the clearance to move freely under the scope.  The bolt handle and body were polished to a high-shine finish.
			 
			For optics we mounted a Sniper Precision Optics 4-16x50mm scope.  Features include a red or green illuminated reticle, locking windage and elevation adjustments, and a removable sun shade.
			 
			To increase the precision of the platform, we installed a Timney Trigger on the receiver.  The light, crisp, 2.5 lb pull has to be felt to be believed.  The action was then fit and installed into a Pro Mag Archangel Mosin Nagant stock.  This new-age, ergonomically friendly, composite stock features a fully adjustable length-of-pull and cheek rest, a small storage compartment, and accepts the included 5-round detachable magazine (10-round mags are available as well).  A Caldwell tilting bipod rounds out the whole package.
			 
			Each of these rifles is fully tested and absolutely ready to fire and enjoy.  If you are looking for a time-tested, heavy caliber, attractive, long range precision target rifle that fires cheap and readily available ammunition while costing hundreds less than the alternatives, purchase one now, or contact us about building one of these custom rifles for you!
			 
	DETAILS:	 
	Model:	Velocity Works Sniper Mosin Nagant (Round Receiver)
	Caliber:	7.62x54R
	Action:	Bolt-Action
	Capacity:	5
	Overall Length:	50"
	Barrel Length:	28"
	Optics:	Sniper Precision Optics 4-16x50mm, Illuminated reticle, locking windage and distance adjustments
	Stock:	Pro Mag Archangel Stock, adjustable cheek rest and length, tan/black, Caldwell Bipod
	Trigger:	Timney, 2.5 lbs pull
	Includes:	(1) 5-round magazine, bayonet, cleaning rod

			Repair and part replacement for all types of firearms
	Is your gun not cycling correctly, locking up randomly, or not ejecting cases easily. It can all be due to a broken, missing or worn part. We can esses the functioning of your gun to find the problem and repair it correctly and safely. The correct function and safe operation of your firearm is our primary concern.
			Common repairs are:
				Broken or worn firing pins
	Worn gun hammers, triggers, or sears
	Missing or broken springs and pins
				Bent or broken extractors
	Cracked stocks
	Firing pin safety
			If you are not sure about something on the way your gun is functioning, feel free to contact us with a description of the issue, and we'll do our best to explain if something is wrong, and what the solution may be. There is no fee for contacting us with questions.
			The amount of work involved in a repair can vary greatly, and we may not be able to give an accurate quote without examining the gun and knowing exactly what the problem is.

            				DESCRIPTION:	 
	Grand Power pistols are all made on 4140 steel reinforced polymer frames with a significant design emphasis on ergonomics and ease of function. Each pistol has an integral Picatinny rail in the frame and comes with (3) interchangeable backstraps, so it is like having a handgun that is custom made for you! Attention southpaws! Each pistol is fully ambidextrous, the slide lock, mag. release and safety are fully functional on both sides of the frame - right out of the box - no modifications required! All of the barrels are high quality stainless steel and use a patented rotating lock, rather than tilting, during cycling for super smooth work at the range. The trigger has a very short reset, so accurate and fast follow-up shots are a breeze. The slide and the steel reinforcing in the frame is finished by nitrocarburizing. This creates a deep, matte non-reflective finish that is actually as hard as tool steel, for unsurpassed ruggedness.
	DETAILS:	 
	Model:  K100	 
	Caliber:  9MM	 
	Action:  Single/Double	 
	Capacity:  15+1	 
	Unloaded Weight:  24 oz	 
	Overall Length:  7.97 in	 
	Barrel Length:  4.5 in	 
	Frame Material:  Polymer	 
	Sights:  3-dot fixed	 
	Grips:  Interchangeable back straps	 
	Finish:  Blued slide	 
	Includes:  (2) 15-round magazines

			At Velocity Works we want to make your gun buying experience enjoyable. Our expert sales staff and on-site gunsmith are here to answer all your questions, without waiting for your number to be called.
			 
			We have competitive pricing on firearms, ammunition, shooting gear and accessories. If we don't have something in stock we are happy to order it for you. Our inventory includes new and used pistols, revolvers, rifles, and shotguns. If there is a new, classic, or collectable gun that you have been looking for let us help you find it.
			 
			Our used guns come with a Velocity Works warranty. Each used firearm we get in is disassembled, cleaned, and inspected before it goes for sale. Something you won't get from a gun show.
			 
			We are the only gun store in Columbus Ohio that sells custom guns. We can customize a handgun, rifle, or shotgun to your specifications. Creating a firearm that is uniquely yours.
			 
			Our clients include a number of law enforcement professionals and military personnel. We offer special pricing to those who are serving to protect us.

Velocity Works, LLC offers a very convenient Lay-away Plan for our customers. The policies and procedures for our “Lay-away Plan” are as follows:
	Only firearms are eligible for this program.
	Lay-away Agreement(s) require a minimum initial non-refundable deposit of (20%) twenty percent.
	$200 minimum purchase is required.
	During the 60-day period, you may make several smaller payments or one final payment at the end of the 60 days.
	Custom Order(s) or orders for merchandise not in current stock may NOT (at Velocity Works, LLC discretion) be ordered until Eighty percent (80%) of the TOTAL amount of the Velocity Works, LLC Lay-away Agreement(s) is paid.
	Velocity Works, LLC will give store credit for any Lay-away deposit and subsequent payments, if any, when, before the end of the Lay-away period the Buyer wishes to apply their layaway to a different product. This is only applicable if the original Lay-away Agreement(s) was NOT for a USED product or if it is a Custom Order, and the order for the product has not yet been placed with the distributor by Velocity Works, LLC.
	Velocity Works, LLC will refund any payments, NOT including non-refundable deposit and or service fee(s) (if any), provided the Lay-away Agreement(s) was for product not normally stocked in store (ie. custom ordered product) and has NOT yet been ordered.
	Should Buyer be unable to successfully complete a NICS Background Check, Velocity Works, LLC will refund any payments, NOT including non-refundable deposit, or service fee(s), if any.
	Lay-away Agreement(s) will terminate, and BUYER’s deposit and other payments under Lay-away Agreement(s) will become NON-REFUNDABLE and be FORFEITED to Velocity Works, LLC if payment is not received on or before the sixtieth (60th) day of the date of signed Lay-away Agreement(s). There will be no exceptions.
	There are NO REFUNDS of any Lay-away Agreement(s) payments beyond what is stated in this agreement.
	All Lay-away Agreement(s) require that the Lay-away Agreement(s) document be signed and dated.
CONSIGNMENT :
Consignor agrees to place the items listed below on consignment with Velocity Works, LLC to try to sell them under the terms of this agreement. Velocity Works, LLC agrees to accept the items listed for consignment sale under the terms of this agreement. Velocity Works, LLC will:
	Inspect all of the items listed in this agreement, and will determine condition and functionality.
	Write up the description and specifications necessary in order to offer the items for sale.
	Will advertise and offer the items for sale as it deems appropriate.
When the items consigned are sold and final payment is made by the buyer, the Consignor will receive their net amount within 30 days. The Consignor represents that they are the rightful owner of the items listed, and that the items are free of any encumbrance. The Consignor agrees that, as Velocity Works, LLC is required to complete all inspections and specifications, prepare the items for sale, and advertise the items, that the items consigned will be left on consignment with Velocity Works, LLC for a minimum of 60 days.
 
After 60 days, if not sold, consignor must pick up firearm or renew agreement in person within 15 days. After 15 days a $5.00 per daystorage fee will be assessed, NO EXCEPTIONS! If firearm is not picked up within 30 days after agreement expires, the firearm becomes property of Velocity Works, LLC.While this agreement is in effect, Consignor agrees to grant the exclusive right to market and sell the items listed below to Velocity Works, LLC.
 
ALL ITEMS MUST BE IN GOOD CONDITION AND CLEAN: Consignee reserves the right not to display any consigned item found on close inspection to be defective. Such items not reclaimed by the consignor within five days of notification, the firearm will become property of Velocity Works, LLC.
 
LIABILITY: Consignee shall not be liable to Consignor for any loss or damage suffered to Consignor's merchandise, including, but limited to, loss or damage to such merchandise from fire, theft, or other casualty. Consignor hereby releases Consignee to the fullest extent possible from any and all claims or any nature in connection with or arising from the placement of Consignor's merchandise with Consignee. Consignor further covenants that he/she shall make no claim against Consignee or Consignee's insurance carrier for any damage to Consignor's merchandise.
 
If the Consignor decides to have consigned items returned, Federal Law requires that the Consignor complete all appropriate forms as if they were purchasing the firearms and pass the NICS background check and consignor agrees to pay Velocity Works, LLC $25.00 for transfer fees. If consignor fails either the documentation or NICS check the firearm becomes the permanent property of Velocity Works, LLC.
 
Store only consignment fee shall be 15% of the selling price of the item. Fees for other services provided by Velocity Works, LLC (e.g.cleaning or repair) or for services provided by third-party vendors are additional and are not included in the consignment fee.
Online Sales only are available for 20% commission, plus auction fees. A $10.00 upfront charge for online auction is non-refundable for firearm storage, unless firearm sells. All firearms will be listed with the reserve at the consignor’s minimum acceptable price, plus 20%. Auction must be finalized for payment to be released.
 
Store with Online Sale is available for 25% of the selling price, plus auction fees. All firearms will be listed with the reserve at the consignor’s minimum acceptable price, plus 30%. Auction must be finalized for payment to be released.
 
After 15% in-store, 20% online or 30% in store with internet, plus auction fees is deducted from selling price, a check will be issued for the remaining balance to consignor. If consignor does not pick up check within 14 days, check will be mailed to their address of record on file via U.S.P.S. for an additional fee of $5.00.
